Female terminalia: Tergite 7 with deep posteromedial emargination. Four spermathecae in two pairs, each pair close together on short ducts, touching but not fused; spermatheca smooth, broadly cylindrical, with a broad basal invagination and a small smooth, cylindrical cap (evagination) distally, cap about 0.25X spermathecal diameter. One specimen (
Pernambuco
) contains five large, elongate, strongly granulose eggs, each about ¼ length of abdomen.
